# Cyberland — UI JSON authoring

Retained HUDs use **separate** files from scenes: **`Content/Ui/<name>.json`**, loaded by **`IUiRuntime`** when the scene’s **`cyberland.engine/ui-document-root`** lists **`uiPath`**.

## File shape

```json
{
  "schemaVersion": 1,
  "root": {
    "type": "cyberland.engine/vertical-stack",
    "id": "hud.root",
    "layout": { "preset": "stretchAll" },
    "children": [ ]
  }
}
```

- **`root`** applies to the existing **`UiDocument.Root`** panel (layout + **`children`** only — do not nest a second full-screen root).
- Per-node fields: **`type`**, optional **`id`**, anchors, **`margin`** / **`padding`**, **`layout.preset`**, type-specific keys (flat on the node).
- **`id`** is unique within the file; used for **`UiElementLookup`** after spawn. **Not** the same as scene entity **`logicalId`**.

## Engine element types (`cyberland.engine/…`)

| Slug | Notes |
|------|--------|
| `panel`, `vertical-stack`, `horizontal-stack` | `spacing`, `backgroundColor`, `backgroundTexture` (`white`, `defaultNormal`) |
| `grid` | `columnCount`, `spacing` |
| `scroll-view` | `content` subtree (not `children` of viewport); `wheelScrollPixels` |
| `image` | `sourceTexture`, `tint` |
| `text-block`, `label` | `text` or `locKey` + `isLocalizationKey`, `fontFamily` (`UiSans`, `Mono`, or full id e.g. `fonttest.jost`), `sizePixels`, style flags |
| `button` | `normalBackground`, `pressedBackground`; optional child `text-block` |
| `radio-button` | `groupId`, `optionId`, `width`, `height`, tints |

Register custom types: **`context.Ui.RegisterElementDeserializer("your.mod/widget", …)`** before spawn.

## Layout presets (`layout.preset`)

`stretchAll`, `stretchWidthAutoHeight`, `topStretch` (+ `height`), `topLeftFixed`, `centerFixed`, `topRightFixed`, `bottomRightFixed` (+ `width`, `height`, `margin`, optional `anchoredPosition` override).

## Mod workflow (after scene spawn)

```csharp
var hud = world.RequireSingleEntityWith<HudRootTag>("HUD root");
if (!context.Host.UiDocuments.TryGetElements(hud, out var ids))
    throw new InvalidOperationException("UI not attached.");
var score = ids.Require<UiTextBlock>("hud.score");
```

Events, simulation, and dynamic strings stay in C# systems — not in JSON.

